args.canonical_rel_desc: Connects an organism or life stage to a biological process in which it participates, contributes, or which it undergoes as part of its life cycle or functional role.
args.justification: These relations link butterfly life stages to life cycle or developmental processes they undergo (butterfly life cycle, molting). Other instances in this chunk that represent the same general semantics already use the canonical_rel_name 'participates_in_biological_process' with a description that explicitly covers both participation and undergoing. Unifying the first two relations to this canonical predicate removes an unnecessary split between 'undergoes_biological_process' and 'participates_in_biological_process' and yields a single, coherent participation predicate for biological processes.
